dt: {bc}any of numerous usually largely gray or brownish oscine birds (family Laniidae) that have a hooked bill, feed chiefly on insects, and often impale their prey on thorns

et: perhaps from Middle English {it}*shrik{/it}, from Old English {it}scrīc{/it} thrush; akin to Middle English {it}shriken{/it} to shriek
shortdef: any of numerous usually largely gray or brownish oscine birds (family Laniidae) that have a hooked bill, feed chiefly on insects, and often impale their prey on thorns

dt: {bc}a large-headed gray shrike ({it}Lanius ludovicianus{/it}) of North America with a black mask around the eyes

shortdef: a large-headed gray shrike (Lanius ludovicianus) of North America with a black mask around the eyes

dt: {bc}a black-and-white European shrike ({it}Lanius senator{/it}) with a red crown and nape

shortdef: a black-and-white European shrike (Lanius senator) with a red crown and nape —called also woodchat
